'''Orowood Tower''' was a thirty-eight story apartment building in [[Orowood]], [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]],<ref name="Specter of the Past">''[[Specter of the Past]]''</ref> with a fantastic view of the [[Manarai Mountains]]. The [[Solo family/Legends|Solo family]] once owned a small apartment there on its thirtieth floor, its second floor had a large shopping center, its third floor held landing pads, and its fourth floor contained five [[Tapcafe/Legends|tapcafes]].<ref name="V">''[[Vision of the Future]]''</ref> It was built in the [[Alderaanian style/Legends|Alderaanian style]], as it had originally been planned to be the first building in a shelter for those who survived the [[Destruction of Alderaan/Legends|destruction of Alderaan]]. However, Coruscant was never popular with the Alderaanians, and after the [[Siege of Coruscant]], the remaining Alderaanian refugees also left, and the Tower became a residential building for the rich.<ref name="Specter of the Past" />

In [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]], several years after the death of [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]], [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] came to Orowood Tower to report to [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] that Thrawn was still alive. The Solos did not believe Calrissian, even though Calrissian claimed to have met with Thrawn. In reality, Thrawn was still dead, and the person Calrissian met with was [[Flim (Human)|Flim]], a con man who impersonated Grand Admiral Thrawn.<ref name="Specter of the Past" />

